<title>USA: NYMEX to raise crude oil futures margins.</title>
<headline>NYMEX to raise crude oil futures margins.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>New York Mercantile Exchange said it will increase the margins on its light, sweet crude oil futures contract at the close of business Wednesday.</p>
<p>Margins will be raised to $1,700 from $1,500 for clearing members, to $1,870 from $1,650 for members and to $2,295 from $2,025 for customers.</p>
<p>Volatility in crude futures surged to above 40 percent from just over 20 percent two weeks ago.</p>
